1:
Rescue me from my enemies, my God;
\q set me on high away from those who rise up against me.
\q

7:
See, they belch out with their mouths;
\q swords are in their lips,
\q for they say, "Who hears us?"

8:
But you, Yahweh, laugh at them;
\q you hold all the nations in derision.
\q

10:
My God will meet me with his covenant faithfulness;
\q God will let me see my desire on my enemies.
\q
